My spouse and | are renova-
ting our home. We have added
a combination family room and
office. plus a darkroom and a
laundry room. We had planned
long hours for this time and early
in May we started.


Workmen came innocently with
hammer. nails, cement, pliers,
wood. paper, rulers and pipes.
First. the existing back porch
was torn up a bit. Not all was
destroyed. just enough to give the
house that "could be a small
earthquake Look.


Next, some trenches we're dug.
They looked too small for what
we planned. Then, cement was
poured and the floors we're
smoothed.


A man came one bright day and
placed the doors and entrances
markers. Within a week some
thing resembling our planned ad-
dition was Undertaking.


After four weeks Of breathing
wood shavings and battling flies
and other insects let in with the
doors opening SO often. have
had enough.


Since May 2lst the heat pump
has helped me maintain some
composure. We rid ourselves of
the evaporative cooler and two
separate air conditioning units.
The last two summers we're spent
in the bedroom and the den where
the units whizzed all day and
night. We felt like clustered
monks from May until October.


Now we can move about from
room to room and feel grand with
a constant cool temperature.


Even the comfort of the heat
pump vanishes when look at the
piles of color charts. Samples of
floor and wall coverings, swat
ches of drapery materials and
other various decorating objects.

colors. tints. subtints, shades,
